     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="4"/>
   <head>ON THESE LOCKES.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>
         <hi>LOckes,</hi> Ornament of Angels, Diadems</l>
      <l>Which the triumphing Quires aboue doe crowne:</l>
      <l>Rich Curles of Bountie, Pinnions of Renowne;</l>
      <l>Of that immortall Sunne immortall Beames.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>
         <hi>Lockes,</hi> sacred <hi>Lockes,</hi> no, adamantine Chaines;</l>
      <l>Which doe shut vp, and firme together binde</l>
      <l>Both that Contentment which in Life wee finde,</l>
      <l>And Blisse which with vnbodied Soules remaines.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Faire <hi>Locks,</hi> all <hi>Locks</hi> compar'd to you (though gold)</l>
      <l>Are <hi>Comets-Locks,</hi> portending Harme and Wrath;</l>
      <l>Or bauld <hi>Occasions-Locke,</hi> that none can holde:</l>
      <l>Or <hi>Abasaloms,</hi> which worke the Wearers death.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>If hencefoorth Beautie e're my Minde subdue,</l>
      <l>It shall (deare <hi>Locks</hi>) be for what shines in you.</l>
   </lg>
   <bibl>
      <hi>W. D.</hi>
   </bibl>
</div>
